    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-06T04:11:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-06T04:11:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-05T18:41:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-05T18:41:00Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough over far western SA linking to a weak front south of the Bight will continue to move over western and southern parts of SA during today. A high pressure system will move south of the Bight early in the week, before another trough and upper level system develops in the west and moves across mid to late in the week, with a vigorous cold front to follow later Thursday and into Friday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds northeast to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning then tending southeast to southwesterly in the early afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures in the low to mid 30s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:10am to 3:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 8 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 36.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then tending northwest to northeasterly during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 15 and 22 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 37.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers south of Yunta, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Leigh Creek in the morning and afternoon. Winds northwest to northeasterly 25 to 40 km/h tending northwesterly during the day then tending northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 19 and 23 with daytime temperatures reaching 33 to 38.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
